# IPython
profile_default/
ipython_config.py

# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is generally handled by the user. In contrast, a python application or function
#   might benefit from knowing the exact python version used for development.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install them. In that case, the lock file should be added to .gitignore.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock
#   .python-version

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
#pdm.lock
#   .pdm-python
#   .pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/frenzyryz/venvs or github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

